						<summary>

						<p>Pāṇḍya, Vīrapāṇḍya, 29th year = A.D. 1325.</p>						

						<p>This records a deed of asylum <hi rend="italic">(āsaṟiya-pramāṇam)</hi> given to the ūrār of Peruṅgaḷūr in Teṉ-Paṉaṅgāḍu-nāḍu a unit of Jayasiṅgakulakāla-vaḷanāḍu, by two <hi rend="italic">araiyar</hi> members of Vattāṇḍār-Kōṭṭai. In return for getting the protection, the two <hi rend="italic">araiyas</hi> promised to give some specified quantity of paddy to the ūrār.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">IPS</hi>, No. 615]</p>						

						</summary>
